ing into the current dynamic report following my second attempt. It seems like it might include MainInvoker coverage, but there's a false indication from the DatabaseManager (DBM). The user data says false, so no action is needed there. I might want to test within the same class using `new DatabaseManager().destroy()`. I'm considering how the Applet constructor might affect things, especially since the Applet is deprecated. There are questions about coverage and if the JaCoCo agent will work as expected.\\n\\n**Clarifying testing requirements**\\n\\nI'm thinking about whether one-to-one mapping needs a test class named `DatabaseManagerTest`. I've done that. There’s a chance new tests might be in the wrong package path since the target root is `tests/src/.../src/test/java`. My final output should be concise, but the unknown source complicates that. The user asked for modifications, so I’m considering writing an \\\"evidence\\\" test to verify HSQLDB tool lookup, but I can't access the private `HELP_TEXT`. Maybe I can use the public `DatabaseManager.main(\\\"--help\\\")` output instead? I have to ensure no direct reflection in tests, though.\\n\\n**Exploring MainInvoker behavior**\\n\\nI need to consider that MainInvoker might be invoking `main` reflectively. However, since the `DatabaseManager` main method has a `--help` option, it may return before executing `new DatabaseManager`. Still, the class initialization occurs before calling main. It seems potential issues arise because `Class#forName` in `<clinit>` isn’t executed when the class is initialized at native-image build time. But the JVM’s coverage report suggests it does execute. I’m wondering if the native image build could select `--initialize-at-build-time` for everything instead?\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_06d4152379d908aa016a119ae5f3a08196975d1a385bec6a81\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABqEZsK8z0DdGBZG2RjYNoF7WD_TkV7zyN9yAGs2k_NDSQITkiY4KYY5hTk3AYz